description: Contains elements that can be used to collect laboratory test results that are routinely administered in clinical trials of pharmacological interventions to assess participant/subject safety, and to record when samples were collected for each participant/subject

cdes.cdeName: Lab panel category
cdes.definitionDescription: Category or panel of lab tests, often logically grouped according to type of testing (Hematology, Chemistry, Urinalysis) or specimen type (Blood, Urine, CSF)
cdes.instructions: Choose the lab panel that was performed
cdes.aliasesForVariableName: Aliases for variable name not defined

cdes.aliasesForVariableName: Aliases for variable name not defined

cdes.cdeName: Lab specimen collection date and time
cdes.definitionDescription: Date (and time if applicable and known) when the specimen was collected
cdes.instructions: Record the date/time according to the ISO 8601, the International Standard for the representation of dates and times (http://www.iso.org/iso/home.html).  The date/time should be recorded to the level of granularity known (e.g., year, year and month, complete date plus hours and minutes, etc.).

cdes.instructions:
Record the date/time according to the ISO 8601, the International Standard for the representation of dates and times (http://www.iso.org/iso/home.html).  The date/time should be recorded to the level of granularity known (e.g., year, year and month, complete date plus hours and minutes, etc.).

crfModuleGuideline: Pulmonary Assessment Master Outline and Guidelines for Use
description: The Pediatric NMD Pulmonary Assessment Master Outline is intended to provide a comprehensive overview of data elements comprising a complete pulmonary assessment for a study patient. Such an assessment includes data from a variety of clinical areas, including a patient's Demographics, History, Physical Exam, Diagnostic Test Results and Therapeutic Interventions.
Contains data elements for the SF-36 instrument [Examples of CDEs included: In general would you say your health is and compared to one year ago, how would you rate your health in general now]

description: Wechsler Abbreviated Scale of Intelligence (WASI-IV)
A feasible, reliable, valid and responsive test for measuring walking velocity over 10 meters in people with MS.
Originally designed to test basic mobility skills of frail elderly patients; has since been used in other populations
A brief, standardized, quantitative test of upper extremity function

Originally developed for use in patients with cardiopulmonary disease, but has since been used in a variety of neurological conditions including MS; evaluates the global and integrated responses of all the systems involved during exercise, including the pulmonary and cardiovascular systems, systemic circulation, peripheral circulation, blood, neuromuscular units, and muscle metabolism

description: This form contains all of the general core CDEs and has been duplicated across all of the diseases on the NINDS CDE website.

cdes.cdeName: Birth date
cdes.definitionDescription: Date (and time, if applicable and known) the participant/subject was born
cdes.instructions: Record the date/time according to the ISO 8601, the International Standard for the representation of dates and times (http://www.iso.org/iso/home.html).  The date/time should be recorded to the level of granularity known (e.g., year, year and month, complete date plus hours and minutes, etc.).  Recording date of birth will give the most detailed information required for calculation of age and is recommended as first choice. However, in some studies recording date of birth may elicit discussions on a potential violation of privacy legislation and specifically HIPAA regulations. In these cases, the calculated age should be recorded.

J Neurotrauma. Feb 2007;24(2):259-69. Pediatric-specific reference(s): Anderson V, Catroppa C, Morse S, Haritou F, Rosenfeld J (2005) Functional plasticity or vulnerability after early brain injury. Pediatrics 116:1374-1382

The term “Spanish origin” can also be used in addition to “Hispanic or Latino.”;Could not be determined or unsure;A person not meeting the definition for Hispanic or Latino.;Not reported;
cdes.instructions: Choose one.  Response is obtained by report of the participant/subject or caretaker. cdes.instructions: Choose all that apply.  Response is obtained by report of the participant/subject or caretaker. Collecting information on race may not be allowed in some countries for concerns related to discrimination. In other countries, however, these concerns are considered a reason for recording race in order to guarantee equal access to care. Investigators receiving funding from the US National Institutes of Health (NIH) are required to report the number of subjects enrolled on an annual basis using the racial categories listed.

cdes.aliasesForVariableName: RACE_CAT_TXT

cdes.cdeName: Education year count
cdes.definitionDescription: Number of years of education completed (age 5 and beyond)
cdes.instructions: For years completed, after the age of 5, code the number of years attained (0-30 years), normed to someone moving full time at the usual pace, i.e. a year that was repeated counts as only 1 year and the usual single-year full-time load completed over several years counts as 1 year. Certificate and technical programs do NOT count no matter how specialized.  The number of  years of typical completion of the relevant program is counted. If the subject obtained their education outside the United States, ask about their educational system to estimate the correct coding - Internship, Residency, and Fellowship years are experiential training and do not count.

description: Contains data elements that are collected to describe the medical history of the study population relevant to NMD research. Medical history data are collected to verify the inclusion and exclusion criteria (e.g., no history of cognitive disabilities) and to describe the study population. The Medical History CRF Module captures conditions that EVER occurred at some point in time within a protocol-defined period (e.g., the last 12 months).

cdes.cdeName: Medical history taken date and time
cdes.definitionDescription: Date (and time, if applicable and known) the participant/subject's medical history was taken
cdes.instructions: Record the date/time according to the ISO 8601, the International Standard for the representation of dates and times (http://www.iso.org/iso/home.html). cdes.cdeName: Echocardiogram tissue doppler ejection time

cdes.aliasesForVariableName: Aliases for variable name not defined

cdes.cdeName: Echocardiogram spectral doppler isovolumic relaxation time
cdes.definitionDescription: Isovolumic relaxation time (IVRT) measured using spectral doppler.  IVRT is an interval in the cardiac cycle, from the aortic component of the second heart sound, that is, closure of the aortic valve, to onset of filling by opening of the mitral valve. It can be used as an indicator of diastolic dysfunction.
cdes.aliasesForVariableName: Aliases for variable name not defined
cdes.previousTitle: Echocardiogram spectral doppler isovolumic relaxation time

cdes.cdeName: Echocardiogram tissue doppler isovolumic relaxation time
cdes.definitionDescription: Isovolumic relaxation time (IVRT) measured using tissue doppler. IVRT is an interval in the cardiac cycle, from the aortic component of the second heart sound, that is, closure of the aortic valve, to onset of filling by opening of the mitral valve. It can be used as an indicator of diastolic dysfunction.
cdes.aliasesForVariableName: Aliases for variable name not defined
cdes.previousTitle: Echocardiogram tissue doppler isovolumic relaxation time

cdes.cdeName: Echocardiogram spectral doppler isovolumic contraction time
cdes.definitionDescription: Isovolumetric contraction time measured using spectral doppler. Isovolumetric contraction is a term used in cardiac physiology to refer to an event occurring in early systole, during which the ventricles contract with no corresponding volume change. Record the time it takes for the contraction to occur.
cdes.aliasesForVariableName: Aliases for variable name not defined
cdes.previousTitle: Echocardiogram spectral doppler isovolumic contraction time

cdes.cdeName: Echocardiogram tissue doppler isovolumic contraction time
cdes.definitionDescription: Isovolumetric contraction measured using tissue doppler.  Isovolumetric contraction is a term used in cardiac physiology to refer to an event occurring in early systole, during which the ventricles contract with no corresponding volume change. Record the time it takes for the contraction to occur.
cdes.aliasesForVariableName: Aliases for variable name not defined
cdes.previousTitle: Echocardiogram tissue doppler isovolumic contraction time

cdes.cdeName: ECG assessment date and time
cdes.definitionDescription: Date (and time, if applicable and known) the electrocardiogram (EKG) was administered
cdes.instructions:
Record the date/time according to the ISO 8601, the International Standard for the representation of dates and times (http://www.iso.org/iso/home.html).  The date/time should be recorded to the level of granularity known (e.g., year, year and month, complete date plus hours and minutes, etc.).
Supplemental - Highly Recommended
cdes.aliasesForVariableName: DIAG_EKG_PERF_DT

cdes.aliasesForVariableName: Aliases for variable name not defined

cdes.definitionDescription: Rate measured in beats per minute of atrial contractions recorded in the electrocardiogram (ECG) being reported
cdes.instructions: Record the atrial rate in beats per minute.
cdes.aliasesForVariableName: Aliases for variable name not defined

cdes.cdeName: ECG heart rate
cdes.definitionDescription: Rate in beats per minute of ventricular contractions recorded in the electrocardiogram (EKG) being reported. Also called Heart Rate (HR).
cdes.instructions:
Record the ventricular rate/ heart rate in beats per minute.
Supplemental - Highly Recommended
cdes.aliasesForVariableName: ECG_HEART_RATE

cdes.definitionDescription: Interval in milliseconds (msec) from the start of the P wave to the start of the QRS complex (PR interval)  for the electrocardiogram (EKG) being reported
cdes.instructions: Measure and record the PR interval in milliseconds (msec)
cdes.aliasesForVariableName: ECG_QRS_DUR_VAL

cdes.cdeName: ECG QRS duration
cdes.definitionDescription: Duration in milliseconds (msec) of the QRS complex for the electrocardiogram (EKG) being recorded
cdes.instructions: Measure and record the QRS duration in milliseconds (msec).
cdes.aliasesForVariableName: ECG_QRS_DUR_VAL

cdes.cdeName: ECG QT interval
cdes.definitionDescription: Interval in milliseconds (msec) from the start of the Q  wave to the end of the T wave (QT interval) for the electrocardiogram (EKG) being reported
cdes.instructions:
Measure and record the QT interval in milliseconds (msec).
Supplemental - Highly Recommended
cdes.aliasesForVariableName: ECG_DP_QTI_ASS_VAL

cdes.cdeName: ECG QTc interval
cdes.definitionDescription: Interval in milliseconds (msec) as corrected for the period from the start of the Q  wave to the end of the T wave (QTc interval) for the electrocardiogram (EKG) being reported
